  "prompt": "Meaning of money?",
  "response": "The meaning of money can be understood from various perspectives:\n\n1. Economic perspective:\n- Medium of exchange\n- Store of value\n- Unit of measurement\n- Facilitates trade and economic transactions\n\n2. Practical perspective:\n- Tool for meeting basic needs\n- Means to acquire goods and services\n- Provides financial security\n- Enables access to opportunities\n\n3. Psychological perspective:\n- Symbol of success\n- Source of security\n- Potential for power and independence\n- Measure of personal achievement\n\n4. Philosophical perspective:\n- Not an end in itself\n- A means to an end\n- Can provide freedom or create stress\n- Reflects personal values and priorities\n\n5. Social perspective:\n- Enables social mobility\n- Provides resources for helping others\n- Indicator of economic status\n- Potential for creating social impact\n\n6. Spiritual perspective:\n- Should not define personal worth\n- Can be a tool for positive change\n- Balance between material and non-material wealth\n- Not more important than relationships and personal growth\n\nThe meaning of money varies based on individual context, cultural background, and personal values. While important, it's generally viewed as a tool to support life goals rather than the ultimate goal itself.",
